AFRICA COVID-19 DATA ANALYSIS - INTRODUCTION 1

AFRICA COVID-19 DATA ANALYSIS

The year 2020 was an unprecedented year for the entire universe due to the emergence of the Corona Virus alias Covid-19. This novel coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic caused widespread disruption of lives across the world. The continent of African was not an exception, It's first case was confirmed in Egypt on February 4th, 2020.
This project will help to analyze the rate of infections and the fatality rate in all of Africa - countries and regions at the moment, how cases and deaths change by the week and what can be done to help curb the spread and return normalcy.



PROBLEM STATEMENT

As Africa's first case of COVID-19 was confirmed in Egypt on February 4, 2020, it rapidly spiked to over a million confirmed cases and nearly 24,683 deaths according to the World Health Organization (WHO) by mid-August 2020. The rise of COVID-19 on the continent of Africa has posed many challenges on the health, socio-economic, and political fronts as health facilities are of sub-standards or non-existent in most areas.
